#Text=Good value, clean accommodation with good continental self service breakfast. Great location. Location of the hotel is very close to Termini though we got a shuttle taxi from Fiumicino. Colosseum and Forum are 15 to 20 mins away. Scenic tour buses stop at Termini or 5 mins away at the Church of Santa Maria di Maggiore and take in most of the top 10 sites which you can hop on or off of. Or cheaper route is to buy bus tickets to use from Termini or Repubblica and No 75 takes you all the way down Via Nazionale past stops for Venezia, Trevi, Pantheon, Navone towards St Peter's. . ption and check-in was efficient though lacking a little warmth. We booked a double for us and a twin along the same corridor for children in late teens. Everything was clean. Good size rooms though shower ensuite looking a little tired and very compact - everything functioned well though. Towels were unusual in that they were not the fluffy kind but were the texture of very large cotton tea towels. The temperature was 36 to 38 degrees during our stay and stayed high at night and the towels worked surprisingly well. The air conditioning was a real bonus. The beds looked firm but I'm quite sensitive to firm beds so was pleasantly surprised that I slept very well. kfast was included and very good value. Broadly self service and continental with a real emphasis on sweet danish, croissants and cake. We liked the cereal, muesli, yogurt and fresh breads with cheese and ham. Teenage children loved the Nutella. stay was mainly about being out and about sightseeing and out to dinner, not about lounging . nd in the rooms or bar area so not sure if they had a bar. We would stay here again as a family as it represents very good value, but we might upgrade if we were going with friends and wanted somewhere more luxurious. There are currently road works going on on this road and on weekdays work starts at 8 til 4.30 ish which could ruin it for those who are after a relaxing break. The lift for luggage in our block next door but one to the main entrance, was tiny and could take one person with large luggage. Once in we used the stairs mainly as we were on 1st floor, but this could be a problem for people with mobility problems.
#Text=2 thumbs up! Helpful staff. Near to Roma Termini which is so convenient. No flat iron
#Text=Very Good. Near to metro
#Text=Good. Breakfast was cold and no choises!!!

#Text=Pleasant. The room was nice and clean. The receptionists were all very kind and helpful. Breakfast was very modest. We stayed for four nights and each morning there were just two options for savoury-one type of strangely tasting cheap ham and cheese. Milk in the coffee maker was watered down so even coffee with molk tasted very poorly. The orange juice was fake from concentrate. You would expect more for the price of the room. s in the room was also completely missing blanket, there was just a sheet instead (felt cold for winter nights). ly any sanitaries in the bathroom and just plastic cups to drink did not help to the atmosphere of a pleasant stay either.
#Text=Good. the staff was very friendly. the area at nice it's not very nice

#Text=It was our second time in Italy but this time our location is perfect and accessible for tourist spo. Staff opened the room and collected borrowed cups and kettle between 10-11 pm which supposed to be collected during housekeeping only, and we were out,, staff must not come in to the room during those time. Staff must enter only into the room during housekeeping ?gonly?h

#Text=Good. Really good location to reach all famous places, only few minutes to go to the Termini station. Very friendly staff. Chlorine smell in the bathroom. No big choice of food during the breakfast.
#Text=Good location ! Would reccomment contilia to any travellers . The location is supa ! Think we will travell again ! Breakfast was delicious and our requiremements was met . Very nice
#Text=Excellent. everything was perfect.what a pleasant stuff.everyone was smiling the receptionists,the waiters at breakfast and the housemaids.totally recommend you to stay at contilia hotel.

#Text=Would deffinately return here again. Room was spotlessly clean, lovely staff, nice breakfast to start your day! Towels are provided but they are very thin although they do the trick, so if you want a fluffy bath towel take your own!
#Text=Excellent. Thank you. Everything was fine
#Text=Good. Great stuff
#Text=Better contact the hotel before booking. Good staffs. WiFi too slow, no English channel on TV, shower too small when curtains used, a bit smelly room.

#Text=Didn't feel like a good caring hotel. Location was ideal but there are plenty of Hotels around. Location. Lift available. Initially, we were not given the room that was shown online while booking. The room given instead was below par. We complained to the desk and then were given a proper room. The shower was giving extremely hot scalding water, impossible to take a bath. We informed the desk every day we stayed. They promised to fix it every time but never did. So a bad experience.

#Text=We stayed for 1 night only and that was enough. Good location near termini station and not a long walk to the city centre and Colosseum. The breakfast was very basic, no eggs and the shower was a tiny compartment with a curtain that sticks to your body when you shower. Also the water temperature couldn?ft be adjusted and in our case was way too hot!
#Text=Good. Good location. Great breakfast. The water for the shower was not consistent and at times was cold. The towels were actually like sheets, very thin.
#Text=Good value for money. Location to Termini excellent. Breakfast included was good value. Facility to leave bags after check out. Floor of room above was noisy.

#Text=Adequate accommodation with pleasant staff in a convenient location. The location is good and the staff friendly. Good restaurants in the area at reasonable prices. Breakfast included which was adequate. Multiple entrances to hotel and then to rooms. Basic room with bad lighting. Had to use torch. Inadequate bedside tables. No 'frig. 3 pillows only in room. Bathroom basic with nowhere to put clothes etc. except the floor. Towels thin, ? Cotton, non adsorbent. Shower pressure variable. Limited savoury breakfast.

#Text=Good. Very central! Bar not open. No room service ( despite drinks menu in room, with number to ring for service...). No drinking glasses in room.. Bathroom in need of up dating. Towels in bathroom were like large t - towels! Breakfast very average.....
#Text=ok. Its position in rome. No facilities for hot drinks after breakfast. On if the single rooms was so small i had difficulty using the toilet.
#Text=Excellent. Staff were very helpful and friendly, nothing was a problem to them,. I thought price of ?85 euro for taxi that they use to airport was very overpriced.
#Text=we enjoyed our stay.I will recommend it. convenient to train station. very nice
#Text=It was ok but not worth the money we paid for it. Location. That it dident have a jug for coffee n tea making in the room.And the breakfast was very plain .
#Text=Was very good and comfortable. Near the station. Quit at night. Breakfast was very good.... Towels
#Text=Clean and ok. Small room. Would like brown bread, grain bread. Does that exist in Italy? And english speaking tv-channels.
#Text=Good. Small. Clean. Bed. Location
#Text=Very Good. central location. bed quite old, room a bit small, bathroom quite small

#Text=Clean noisy spacious but also thieving. Room was spacious and clean breakfast was ok. Such a noisy street the dog across the way was barking all night. The shops under the hotel were open till late but the ppl were screaming. They wanted taxes upfront in cash she sent me to a bank at the end of the street. The machine was broken the guy said he can give it over the counter. He said it's the same as the bank. He swiped my card and wanted to charge me ?46 fee for taking ?200 from my bank. When I said no his female partner was nervous anyway I refused and went back to the hotel I told the receptionist she looked at me stupid. I said u send ppl to the bank to get ripped off. If u want customers send them to safe places not thieving ppl. The hotel was sharing rooms with 3 other hotels. I could not understand that at all. 3 different entrances our was hotel campigola
#Text=Nice and handy to transport. The room was large. That you don't actually stay in the hotel. You actually have to go a few doors up at a different hotel.

#Text=overall the positives were in excess of the negatives and would I go back again ? Yes we would. The images presented on line were generally accurate but some areas of the hotel in particular the access to the llifts and the area on the first floor (especially the leather sofa ) were a litte jaded ! The room was a little on the small for my liking but the rooms were spotless and cleaned thoroughly every day. The staff were extremely helpful especially the front desk staff , The breakfast was also boaring for the most part and on a couple of mornings there were outages of milk, coffee and cutlery. The location for my wife and I was very good . close to the main central bus/train station and for those hopon/off buses that ply their trade through the Roman streets. Lots of lovely restaurants in the locality to suit every budget.

#Text=Pretty nice hotel. Everything worked, nothing was broken. The recently remodeled bathroom was beautiful. The beds were comfortable and the linens good quality. The room was very clean, we appreciated that. And the front desk staff was helpful and friendly. Even though not close to any Roman antiquities, the street of the hotel had many nice restaurants to offer. Size of the room was very small and it looked depressing with mostly dark colors. It didn't help that the old style LED bulbs needed much time to light up. The quality of the breakfast was marginal There were a lot of food choices but all were overly processed and not fresh. We found little we wanted to eat or drink.
#Text=Good. Spacious and clean. Noisy surrounding

#Text=For 3 stars hotel its very gd. Perfect Location, very close for termini station 4 min walk, close for some attractions like colosseum 15 min walk, the staff are nice, breakfast was good, and very gd restaurants in the area. Towels quality, they were very clean but thin more like piece of cloth. It was not easy to equalise hot and cold water in the shower
#Text=Wifi was so weak, I could not use it. Staff was nice. A little overpriced. Staff, location

#Text=Very Good. the location is excellent. middle of city, near to main station Termini. The facility were good like bed, washroom, lift. Towels were good and clean. Price would have been a little less

#Text=Great location for. People at the front desk were very helpful. Very close to the main Subway Station. The neighborhood is a little bit sketchy, but there are some good restaurants in the immediate vicinity of the hotel.

#Text=Overall we had a great time in Rome and generally speaking our stay was relaxing. Good location for restaurants. Clean and comfortable. Breakfast was average. Initially we had an issue with unlocking the main door to our room, however once shown how to unlock it was fine. This could have been avoided if we were made aware of this when being issued with the keys.

#Text=Pleasant. The first time we arrived on September 9 and lived in room number 207. Everything was very pleasant. Beautiful interior, beautiful view from the balcony, near the sights and the station. Attentive staff of the reception desk. The second visit to the hotel was disappointing. We were settled with the girl first into the room with two separate beds, although we asked for one large in the reservation. Then gave the number 105 where there were two matched beds, which were constantly dispersed at night. Only 3 channels worked on TV, even the music was not listened to.We asked the staff of the reception desk to give us tomorrow morning with us, since we left at 7am to the airport, and breakfast at 7:30 began. But he replied that only one croissant could give us. I worked in a hotel and I know perfectly well that they always give a box of breakfast with yoghurt, fruit and rolls, as the kitchen starts working a few hours before breakfast starts. During the departure, the staff of the reception desk paid no attention to us and did not even give the promised croissant. The phone to call and remind him in our room did not work. I'm very sorry that I do not want to stop with you any more and demand to answer me about such an incomprehensible attitude to our visit.
#Text=I would recommend my friends stay there, we had an awesome visit to Rome. Location great. Close to train station. Streets around hotel. A lot of garbage

#Text=Excellent. Breakfast was very good, with enough options for everyone. Wifi connection was stable. It is really close to the main station which made it easy to get around and to leave on the last day. It isn?ft that we didn?ft like, but at first it was a bit weird because we were taken to another place a couple doors down the street and we weren?ft expecting that. However, it didn?ft really make a difference on our stay.
#Text=Neat but overpriced. The staff were very friendly and helpful. For the price the bathrooms could have been bigger. There was water blockage in the shower.
#Text=Good. Breakfast was very good, nice coffee too. Close to the termini which was important to us. All good, we stayed here 3 years ago.
#Text=Excellent. Location. Quiet. Helpful staff. Room was very tight.
#Text=Convenient location but basic stay! Location. Very basic bathroom and bedroom.

#Text=It was pleasant, could have been more accomodating to the customers needs. Staff were extremely helpful and friendly. The beds were single beds, could have been a double bed. The towels were like table cloths, very thin and not a proper towel. We had to leave early morning (before 7am) on 4 days of the 6 night stay, as we either had to catch a train, or leave early to drive to a distant location, and breakfast only started at 07h30am. When we asked if they could not give us something to eat, or a breakfast pack or something, they said no sorry the kitchen lady only starts at 7am??? This is strange as other establishments were able to give us a breakfast pack for missing breakfast. We paid for bed and breakfast.
#Text=Great location and great for termini. Location was great,also great restaurant nearby.
#Text=Excellent staff, plenty of restaurants nearby. The 24 hour reception. Not enough plugs in room
#Text=Very Good. Nice and kind staff. Good breakfast, plenty of variety. Location is quite convenient close to Termini station. Bed was quite hard, so it was a bit difficult to sleep.

#Text=Personal information is at risk here. They have good things but the experience with the passport totally made me hate them. When checking in the receptionist asked for my passport and didnt give it back until next day without any reason. Another staff member gave it to one of the persons in my group. That is totally unprofessional and risky because all my personal information is there. I so so hated they did that.
#Text=Good. It was clean, staff were helpful and friendly, and the breakfast was very good. Restaurants nearby were good.

#Text=Will consider other hotels around this location for next time to avoid misleading information. The hotel is not far from the Termini station. From this station, we can easily go to the other monuments by bus or metro. Also for coming or leaving by train, it's really convenience. I saw the photos of this hotel and thought they are nice and comfortable to stay. However, when I arrived, they did not give us the room as showed in photos but a smaller one in another hotel just few walks away. I haven't recognized that until I got the key with another hotel's name on it. I booked this hotel because the photos they show are really nice but in reality, I got another one which is not comfortable as I thought.
#Text=Very Good. Very good location, just 2 min walk away from Roma Termini..  Beds are toooo short, just 1.8 mts...
#Text=No again. The room was clean and comfortable. Receptionists are not willing to help and they are showing that.
#Text=Good. Location. No Iron for clothes

#Text=Good. the property is very clean and location is excellent. the room was small and tiny - breakfast was missing eggs - bread was not fresh enough. they cut the WiFi in the last day early morning before i check out ( if they keep till check out i think there should not be a problem ).
#Text=Very Good. Location, cleanliness. Very small room. Breakfast missing eggs, bread not fresh.

#Text=Pleasant. Good location for access to the train station. Hotel was basic but very clean. Staff did their job but without a smile or any attempt at friendliness! The main issue is that the rooms are very small - the double bed virtually touched the walls - not even enough space to put a suitcase on the floor to open it.
#Text=Good. The property was very close to the train station.
#Text=simply fair. Location its a key cos its 3 minutes away from train station and metro station. Only the location

#Text=Hotel Contilia Rome. It was in an ideal location to public transport, shops, restaurants and tourist activities. The staff were also really friendly, and remembered our faces whenever we went in or out of the hotel to pick up our room keys, which was nice. The floor in the room was a bit dusty and with only 1 thin pillow for each of us the bed wasn't the best on your neck. Breakfast was also a small and limited choice compared to other places I've been.

#Text=Good. Nice and friendly staff. Hotel is close to the train station. Good breakfast. Main attractions are at least a 15 minute walk. Wi-fi was slow. Lots of stairs to get up to your room. Area was not the greatest.

#Text=Good place for a short stay in Rome, convenient location for travel, but could be more comfortable. Located conveniently close walk to the main terminal where you can catch all the buses and use the metro, breakfast was good (especially the pastries!). The A/C was weak for how hot it was in Rome, the towels smelt oddly like vinegar, our room ran out of cold water (somehow?!) and we would have to wait a while for it to come back, the location was convenient but also a bit sketchy so be careful.

#Text=Excellent. The location of the hotel was great. Also a good buffet continental style breakfast. More than enough to set you up for the day ahead. Because I hadn`t been in Rome before I booked a taxi through the hotel to meet us at the airport and take us to the hotel. I was charged 60 euro for that. Once we were traveling about in Rome I wasn`t long in finding out that taxis charged a flat rate of 30 euro for that trip. I also discovered the airport shuttle bus ran to just outside the metro station which was only a 2 min walk from the hotel. That would have cost us only 6 euro.
#Text=Brecfast. Location
#Text=Good hotel in this price. Good location

#Text=Good and bad. Location is easy to go to the airport.Breakfast is delicious. Unfortunately I have to point out that it doesn't looks like pictures anyway Even though the breakfast is awesome.But it charged me 5 euros for printing Bording pass which are totally free in others.And I don't get why reception refuse to charge my phone that I forgot to charge it last night.Because my plug is European standard which was not quite suitable in hotel's restaurant during breakfast time.And I was powered off all day which I only need few mins charging during breakfast ..
#Text=OK. The bed in the room very uncomfortable

#Text=Good. It?fs very close to Termini, so it has easy access to transportation around the city, as well as some shopping and restaurant options. The beds were not the most comfortable, the water coming from the shower could not keep the same temperature for more than a minute, the breakfast was only ok. The building needs more maintenance, and the AC was not nearly strong enough for the size of the room.
#Text=Pleasant. I liked breakfast. It was delicious. And the staff all very kind people. The localization was amazing because was near Termini Station. I lost my notebook.
#Text=Pleasant. No coffee and tea facilities, Breakfast was the basic and ordinary
#Text=Excellent. Location and breakfast. No coffee facilities in the room.

#Text=Pleasant. Breakfast and staff was nice but not very helpful with food suggestions or getting air conditioner fixed. Air conditioner in the room didn't work. We told the staff and all we got was a small fan, they didn't repair it. It was dingy and the bedspread was probably 20 years old.

#Text=Super location, cheap, you get what you pay for. Good value for money. Didn?ft cost a fortune so you need to expect simple basic facilities. The location to Termini was fantastic therefore it?fs location is definitely its best feature. Breakfast was adequate but quite basic best to go early
#Text=Rome is a fascinating city. The location was good, very clean
#Text=Very Good. Room was small but the beds were comfy and the shower was nice. Great location, right beside the main train station. Quiet enough at night but loads of restaurants near by.

#Text="It does what is says on the tin". The room was clean and the breakfast was good. Very convenient location if you need to get to the train station or if you are getting the shuttle bus from the airport. Terrible towels and the room is exceptionally small. Air con isn't the most efficient system I have ever seen.
#Text=Pleasant. Good location Great staff Nice room Nice building. Safe didn't work and wasn't fixed even when mentioned Shower was difficult, temperature kept changing Breakfast indifferent
#Text=Really refreshing two days in a heart of Rome. Beds were little bit hard we managed with it.
#Text=Pleasant. Location is close to the train station. Breakfast and bath towels
#Text=Good. Close by to all major attractions and the Rome Termini.

#Text=Good. Staff was helpful ans kind. The first room was on 2nd floor with smoking smell coming from the shabby bath room. The location was good. Staff was helpful but there wasn't even tea kettle in a room. If you need a hot water, pls refer to the point.

#Text=Good location. Value for money stay. Location Central, a 5 minute walk from the main train station Termini. Has a number of eating joints close by, which remain open till pretty late. Room Family rooms are pretty big in size. It?fs originally an apartment complex so the rooms are decent in size. Bathrooms are neat and clean and we did not face any issues with the basic amenities. Breakfast Good breakfast with decent variety. The different types of cakes were a real delight to have. Spacious breakfast area. Breakfast starts at 7am, so keep that in mind if you are planning an early check out. Service Courteous and helpful staff at the reception. Had to pay city tax in cash
#Text=Good value and excellent location to the train station. Front desk personnel was very helpful & friendly. Morning breakfast staff a bit grumpy.
#Text=Pleasant. The room given to us was very different from posted photos online. The shower was smaller than a phone booth

#Text=Lovely staff and breakfast was plenty of choice it?fs just the staff door which was annoying. The room we had was next to a staff door for something and it was so loud from slamming where people was going in and out it would wake us up at 6:30am it?fs okay if you can get back to sleep but my partner struggled.
#Text=Good. Excellent location .. 5 min walk to termini station. Breakfast was not that good for us. Not too tasty. No eggs ...
#Text=Short and sweet. Friendly and informative service. Staff was able to guide guest well. Rooms could have been slightly bigger. Breakfast could include eggs
#Text=Pleasant. Basic...nothing fancy but clean and easy walk from Termini ( less pedestrian traffic if you go sown length of station for a few blocks and cross there.

#Text=would happily stay there again! Brilliant location to Termini station, lots of eateries nearby, clean, comfy bed and room was a few doors down from main hotel which was no issue, great courtyard, lift and very easy to access.
#Text=We will be back???? Everything was walking distance! Bathroom needs more attention around the shower!!

#Text=Very Good. Location location location. A few minutes from Termini station and easy access to all the main attractions of Rome. Expect an extra ?4 per person per night charged in cash on arrival. Always unhappy about unclear costs. Breakfast is included but fairly basic, you're left to get on with things yourself, don't wait to be seated or you'll wait a long time! Property is actually split up and you walk down the road a bit to get to a shared courtyard with rooms.

#Text=Good stay with some disappointments. The location is good near to termini station.The stay was nice , staff special mention for the cleaning lady, everything is good. The room doesn't have charging point. I have to move my bed on the quadruple room to charge my phone
#Text=Enjoyable. Friendly staff, great location, very clean, overall a nice place to stay. No complaints

#Text=Good value, location close to the Rome Central station and not as bad as other reviews make out!! Very close to the station. Good WiFi. Breakfast basic but a good start to the day. We were in the second building and I was worried due to terrible reviews but overall satisfactory. Room was quite dark, beds weren't the comfiest and the towels are AWFUL!

#Text=Great location, hotel was ok. The location is great. The hotel is near the trainstation and all tourist attractions are nearby aswell. The breakfast was really bad organised. Most of the time there was almost nothing to eat and the room was kind of in weird corner of some old hotel.
#Text=Nice . Became sick and left early .told would add phone call charges but no discount for early depar. Could do a little better more American products. No table or chairs to sit in room

#Text=Stay ok room not what was expected. The. The accomodation room 16 did not come near what the puctures on internet looked like . We had to go down the street a few doors to our room was not in main hotel .
#Text=Great central location. Bteakfast was good, view of courtyard from room was loverly. Great central location. Room and bathroom was very small

#Text=WE LOVE ROMA!!! Handy hotel, close to Termini central railway station for easy travel into the city from Fiumicino Airport. Good location for walking in various directions, or taking the Metro, plus lots of local cafes and restaurants. Helpful staff, really no problems considering it is reasonably priced. We stayed six nights, and enjoyed ourselves thoroughly.
#Text=Excellent. Perfect location. Bad wi fi Poor choice in breakfast but maybe that is standart everywhere in Rome
#Text=Good stay. Location was great. Nothing

#Text=Excellent. The location near Termini Station and the staff, and breakfast. Receptionists Fabiola and Nick and the other guys were very helpful in helping me to locate places I wanted to visit. Rooms very small, with no counter space in the bathroom to put your toiletries, makeup etc. Also there is no room to put a large suitcase I had to share my bed with mine.
#Text=Pleasant stay and great time in Rome! Good location, friendly and helpful staff. Breakfast choice could of been better
#Text=Excellent staff, good breakfast, weak coffee and variable bedrooms. Staff. Some of the food. Having stayed there about 5 times the bedrooms and bathrooms very so much from very good to poor.
#Text=Good. It was quaint. Our room was not what was pictured and was small
#Text=Pleasant. Great location. Close to Train station , shopping, and restaurant. The staff were friendly. Small room and shower.

#Text=Only good location, very bad breakfast. The location is excellent. 2 minutes from nearest bus stop and 5 minutes from Roma Termini. Probably the only reason of this hotel being liked by people. The photos can be misleading.. It is a very small hotel room and the bathroom is incredibly small. Very difficult to take a bath as well. Very very bad breakfast. One of the worst breakfasts I have ever had in any hotel.

#Text=Great location, good hotel. Basic but has what you need. Check in was very quick and easy, staff very nice. Room was clean , the second room with pull out sofa was small, but didn't bother us. Location was great, we walked everywhere. A lot of lovely restaurants and coffee bars around. Rooms cleaned every day, change of towels. One night we had a problem with our toilet, rang reception and one of the staff members came and problem was fixed within 5 minutes. Very good service. The breakfast wasn't great, but the kids loved it. A lot of cakes and sweet bread. Would have loved to see more fruits, a few diffrents cheeses and maybe some salami.

#Text=It was ok for what we needed it but would not stay here again. Very good location. Staff very friendly Hotel in very good location close to everything. Room was not ready when arrived and taken to the room by staff Waited 10min for room to be cleaned while sitting outside Room was not the same as on the pictures, it was much smaller and little dark
#Text=Perfect for what we wanted. The location was perfect for the hotel, and the staff were so friendly! The breakfast area was quite cramped, wasn?ft too much choice for breakfast either.

#Text=Convenient and enjoyable. The location close to train station as I had to travel the next day. Within walking distance. The breakfast was very good and and the room had a nice ambience. The curtains in the room didn't quite close but otherwise everything was fine.

#Text=Suitable. Centrally located for our needs and room, linen was clean. Room and bathroom very small. Breakfast average. We stayed in what seemed an annex to the hotel and perhaps would?fve preferred the main hotel.

#Text=Thank you to the receptionists for help regarding the directions:). We enjoyed the fact that the hotel was close to Termini station, which made it easy to have a transfer to and from the airport, get a subway to the Vatican City. The room was spacious enough and had all the necessary facilities. When we entered the room, we smelled chlorum:( However, the room was really clean and the sheets as well as towels were changed every day. I would advise the hotel to be more environmentally friendly and change the towels every two or three days or when people put them on the floor, as a sign to replace them.

#Text=Confortable and well located hotel for great money. Bidet in bathroom, confortable bed matress and pillow, comfortable chairs and couch in reception, very polite staff, big windows, lift, nice decoration. Towels material, shower water temperature difficult to regulate, no egg on breskfast, bad accustic in room do noise from corridor and neighboor room can be heard

#Text=Comfortable and clean good location close to amenities and travel links. Rooms were clean and roomy cleaned every day while we were there. No kettle in the rooms would have been nice to able to make a hot drink if you wanted one
#Text=Excellent location , walked everywhere. Could leave luggage after check out. Lent guests large umbrellas for rainy days. Free safe deposit box. No shower gel
#Text=Great. The breakfast menu is not enough. A simple boiled egg would have been great though. :)

#Text=Excellent. The location of the hotel is perfect, 15min from the Colosseum and Fontana Di Trevi by walk and the train station is just 2 blocks away. The staff were really nice to us and very helpful ! Definitely recommend !
#Text=Very Good. I liked the location because it was convenient very close to Termini. People was noisy and I couldn't sleep well.
#Text=Good. Location was central. Lots of restaurants around and a 5 minutes walk to the station to get around to the sites. Bed was uncomfortable and breakfast was basic.
#Text=Pleasant. Good location. Cleaning Service
#Text=Nice place and good staff. none in particular. none

#Text=Amazing city. Great location for sight seeing and travel. Reception lost our room key 1 morning and tried to blame us but we handed it in, they later found it!! Bit disappointing and only 1 lift holding 3 persons and we were on 5th floor another disappointment.
#Text=Close, comfy and convenient. Proximity to metro. Room smaller than expected, plumbing issues nearby in the hotel that created unpleasant fumes

#Text=Enjoyed our stay .but for the kids would have likes a little more at the breakfast bar. Staff very friendly. Came back to a lovely clean room each day.. Breakfast could have more variety. Bananas would be a plus..more fresh fruit..asserted yorgarts.
#Text=Short break in Rome. Very close to the station. Very small shower
#Text=Overall good value for money. The location. Bath cubicle
#Text=Good. Great location, close to Termini station. Helpful staff.
#Text=Pleasant. Staff are not friendly. Breakfast is routine and WiFi was not good.

#Text=Very Good. Hotel itself is good, good location and close to some attractions. Staff are friendly and breakfast was good, bed is comfy and the bedroom has big windows to the street making the room bright and fresh. Room was small
#Text=Good. Location is good. Room is clean. Convenient
#Text=Good value for money. Location. Bathroom

#Text=Good. Location of the hotel is very convenient, near most attractions. Rooms are let?fs say acceptable, the pictures shown do not represent the real situation - they are photoshop masters :/ Towels and bedsheets are old.

#Text=A nice stay close to the train station. The location is very good. Very close to the train station and underground, so you do not waste time upon arrival or departure. The staff was very friendly and helpful and tried to solve problems promptly, be it connectivity, techs, where to dine, shower, etc. WiFi connection is excellent in lobby or breakfast room. Shower cabin is OK however small. Good price value given the facilities and location. WiFi not always that good in the room.

#Text=Over all a good stay and rome is an excellent stay. We were 5 mins late for checkout and the staff where unawear that we could understand italian. One female staff member said in italian how dare they me late they knew it was 11. Nothing was said in english and we understood where were late and explained we where packing and appoligised, they could of happily charged us a late checkout as we fully understood we where late and was our fault. Whilst the staff member said this the male staff member was smirking after hearing what she said.
#Text=Very enjoyable. Comfortable hotel, very good location and helpful staff.
#Text=Review of Hotel Contilia. The room was clean, well equipped and spacious. The location of the hotel is excellent! The breakfast is a normal continental. We found the internet access cumbersome.
#Text=Excellent. The really awesome breakfast, huge items and the people surroundings were really good! Some continuous bad smell always from the washroom/rest room!
#Text=Very good. The location is great. We always take the hop on bus to first day to get to know the city and it was just only two block away. Beds and decor are not the best
#Text=Pleasant. It wasn't bad, but ... nothing special. I had a room in different building so I had to go to the reception or breakfast through outside.

#Text=Very enjoyable apart from the 2 single beds constantly splitting! Breakfast was enjoyable, staff were very friendly, location was very good to be fair, had some excellent restaurants close by! The room was not the size we thought it would be (from pics), bathroom was cramped and a double bed was 2 singles pushed together that kept splitting apart (quite annoying), Other than it was fine!

#Text=Good. The room was clean and additional blankets were later provided, as it was quite cold inside. The personnel was nice and helpful in every aspect. The breakfast offee was rich. The room was very small. I would prefer more continental kind of breakfast, because the majority of the breakfast offer was sweet.
#Text=Pleasant. It was near to central station and the public tranports and the staff was polite. It needs to be renovate.

#Text=Overall a good hotel for a short stay in Rome. Great location, round the corner from the central train station and within a 20 min walk of all the top sites in Rome! Friendly staff and lots of places to eat and buy gifts near the hotel too. Hot chocolate and coffee ran out, think it was a lack of milk. A shame since we paid for breakfast but don't really eat much and mainly wanted unlimited drinks! Also, not the most modern building (old rickety lift, etc) but overall not bad for a short stay. Would recommend.

#Text=Poor hotel ... Staff friendly. Poor breakfast, dry bread and instead of fresh orange they gave us orange mixed squash with water...bed sheets and towels smells like vinegar.. I don't recomend this hotel

#Text=Nevertheless the overnight stay was ok. Very good location of the hotel since it is near the train station. Clean room and comfortable mattress. Pillows are old and flat and needs to be change. Breakfast was mediocre. Waiter that morning did not even greet coming guest. Since we are in Italy I was expecting espresso or cappuccino apart from the American coffee and juice for breakfast.

#Text=Our stay was great, if you don't need to spend too much time in the room it's perfect. I love the location, the staff and the cleaness. We had to queue to get coffee, the breakfast area was packed with people. The room was a bit too small. We book a twin and we got a double with an additional bed so we didn't have space to put our luggage.

#Text=Good location with clean and functional rooms. The rooms were very basic but clean and functional. The staff were courteous and welcoming. The walk from Rome Termini to the hotel was a bit intimidating that late at night as gangs of youths clearly congregate in the area.

#Text=Good. The staff was very nice and helpful and the room was taken care of every day nicely. Location is the best feature, being close to the Termini Station and other important touristic sites. We were given rooms at the Hotel Campidoglio even though we booked Contilia and the rooms were not as nice as in the pictures. The worst part was the fact that the heat would automatically turn off during the night and it was really cold in the morning.
#Text=Good. Big nice room. Decent breakfast. Simple amenities like iron/chargers were not provided on request.

#Text=A dream vacation to a majical place. The room was nice , love the fabric wallpaper, the front desk was very helpful, and breakfast was tasty, the hotel overall had nice detail and charm, the location was in walking distance to many attractions. shower a little to small for me, but it was sufficient
#Text=Reasonable. OK. The other building where we first got the room.... later they got us in the main building...OK

#Text=Good. This hotel is located nearby railroad Termini station, easily detected. Personal is skilled and polite. The breakfast is good bur not very plenty. Generally this hotel merits its 3 stars. It Looks a little old.Probably it needs a repairing at least cosmetic.

#Text=If you book this hotel make sure your not staying in the building down the road from main hotel. Staff where friendly. We did not stay in the main hotel if I wanted a b&b I would have booked one and not a great selection at breakfast

#Text=Pleasant. Location is the only benefit. Breakfasts definitely need improvement. Plus, the hotel loves locking the main entrance door and we had to wait for more than 5 minutes for a receptionist to return to his desk and open the door for us. WIthout offering apologies for making us wait, by the way.

#Text=Loved Rome and the hotel was very convenient. The location, the hotel reception was open 24 hours, the bed was comfy. The bathroom and shower were tiny- very cramped. The breakfast was limited- too many sweets and cakes and no choice of eggs.
#Text=Good. Reception were always smiley and helpful
#Text=Comfortable room close to the train station! Hotel was convenient to the train station which met our needs. Nothing

#Text=Downhill since we stayedhere a couple of years ago. We are quite neutral on Contilia. The room was OK but nothing special. About the same as the 2 star hotel which we chose to return to. Breakfast OK but nothing special. This is really not a 3 star hotel any more. We were not in the hotel itself but in a building next door that had an open door. This raises security problems in this, not so great area near Termini.
#Text=Value for money. Location which so close to Termini. Bed is too small and the door is very difficult to open. This is a fire risk.
#Text=Pleasant. The room was very smelly
#Text=Great location, very clean room. Room was very clean and looked newly done up. Our room was in a separate building block from the main hotel block where breakfast was.

#Text=I was satisfied with my stay,and would return if I am in Rome again. breakfast was European,not American, but was good. I do not expect American when traveling outside of the USA. WiFi could have been a little better
#Text=great place to saty for acess from the station and to tour the city tourist sights. Breakfast was fresh and plentiful. The orange juice machine, try fresh proper orange juice
#Text=Pleasant. Location

#Text=Good location, hop on hop off bus a must, great city, average hotel. Rome was lovely, location was good ,plenty or restaurants in the area. Hotel staff very not very welcoming, only 3 tv channels working, tea/ coffee facilities in room would of been nice,
#Text=Good. Close to the railway station good price. for Rome room was ok I would stay here again. Nothing really
#Text=Good. Location was good, close to the Main Station.

#Text=It is in a good position, easy access to the station. Breakfast was as expected, plenty of choice for continental. The room was adequate, but the bed wasn't hugely comfortable and the pillows were terrible, flat and hard.
#Text=Satisfied. Location. Very small room, Limited meal choice at breakfast
#Text= ?E Close to termini, quite central. Very noisy at night our room at back of building
#Text=Very Nice Hotel that is Close to Everything! Nice breakfast and service, and very close to the train station and tour buses.

#Text=Pleasant stay at a central hotel. Staff were very helpful and friendly. Good selection for continental breakfast. Centrally located. Exactly what was required at a reasonable cost. No tea or coffee making facilities in room.

#Text=Excellent location for a stopover night. I was there on,y as a stop over for a night. Location near train station was fabulous. Very safe. There are some nice little restaurants around. Hotel staff very helpful for the few hours i had to see things. Breakfast very adequate. Is a long walk, about 45 mins to get to sights, but is nice to wander and see the streets.
#Text=Rome visit. Location, kind personnel, breakfast a most,. Comfort of the bed and pillows, too hard
#Text=Very Good. Location. Clean comfortable helpful staff.
#Text=Basic room. Tiny shower. Good location. Location. Walking distance to lots of monuments. Shower was tiny.

#Text=This Hotel is adequate for a nice stay near to transport and also near to major sights. Room was quite well decorated. Shower worked well and soap/shampoo etc provided. Room was clean and cleaning staff pleasant. Nice pictures in corridors and our room was very quiet. Good choices of sweet breakfast items, filled croissants, cereal, fruit , bread and jam/honey/ cake, two types of juice and a coffee machine with lots of buttons. They ask you to leave your key with reception when you go out. This is advisable because of the number of dippers in Rome. Being asked to pay tourist tax up front in cash. Didn't mind paying for room up front with a card. Room was small, and bathroom cramped, but that is what you can expect at this price point in Central Rome. Breakfast was reasonable, but not much savoury choice, ie no salami or sausages.
#Text=Our stay was good and my daughter enjoyed it. I love their towels?? Few choices of bread
#Text=Good. Location 5 mins from central term in I. Small room extra small shower

#Text=Pleasant. First of all, I would like to highlight the fact that it is in an area easily accessible, although during the night it may be dodgy to go alone around that specific place. Friendly staff and helpful as well. Apart from the good side there is the internet connection, it was snaily slow, with disconnections around the time. Also the shower door was taken away from its place and I had to put it in the right place. Besides this the value for money for the room that I had and its facilities is not that high. Also, in the first day I received a face towel with some weird brownish spots.

#Text=Overall an Ok experience. Location was great and coffee was good. Staff was helpful. The hotel did not provide for any tea in the room. Not much for three stars. The bed was not really comfortable. It was not easy to relax. Breakfast was limited and had no eggs which made it an Ok breakfast. There were lot of condiments with bread, but no sasusages, eggs or bacons.

#Text=The location of the hotel is very good, closed to everything, the staff is very friendly,. The location is very good, closed to everything, the staff is very friendly and the breakfast good enough. I definitely recommend.
#Text=Very unpleasant exce. The room was great except the bathroom was so small it was rediculous. Bathroom so small
#Text=Great place bad beds. The location was great and very quiet. The beds were terriable worst sleep ever
#Text=Very basic. Would have liked kettle in room. Clean. Bed very uncomfortable
#Text=Good. The internet connnection was relatively weak.
#Text=Inexpensive, convenient. Very accommodating staff. Nothing A real old downtown hotel.

#Text=The staff were amazing, the breakfast was nice, however the toilet didn't flush. Could be cleaner. The breakfast was quite good. The staff were all very nice, friendly and helpful. The shower was abit dirty with little bits of hair on the floor and the toilet didn't flush. We needed to call them twice in our 3 days there
#Text=Good. Good location. Clean room. I could not control the shower temperature. It was very cold water or very hot water.
#Text=Good. Location is good, close to station and walking distance to most of the sights. Breakfast, although plenty could have been a bit better...it is Italy, where are the different cold meats.
#Text=Very Good. It was nice and clean .. Air conditioning not very strong
#Text=Very comfortable. The breakfast needed a bit more fruit
#Text=Good. The hotel Contilia is a good choice by price/quality. The location is near the main railway station which helps not to worry if you have an early train.
#Text=Convenient pleasant. The location to public transport excellent. The area close to Termini station dodgy and unsafe but not the hotels fault

#Text=Great value hotel close to the main station. Great value for money. This was our first time in Italy and thus I appreciated arriving into Rome and staying at a hotel so easily accessible by train and easy to find. The breakfast was good. It is a less upmarket part of town. But to be honest this was of no great concern.
#Text=Comfortable stay. Room was comfortable, staff most helpful. The shower was very small, hard to get into

#Text=Clean and near Termini. OK hotel for the price, also very convenient by the Termini. Busy at check-in but ok service. Not overfriendly though. You don't feel welcome, but maybe not expected at this kind of hotel. No lactose- and glutenfree options at breakfast but when I asked I got glutenfree cookies.
#Text=Excellent. Location. Near by restaurants and train station. Needs more breakfast options.
#Text=Not at all bad. Good airconditioning. Slightly preremptory staff
#Text=Pleasant. Location. That we was in a block of building not in a hotel.

#Text=Great location and hotel. The location was great, very close to termini station and a short walk to the colosseum. The hotel itself was very pleasant and comfortable, and the staff were very friendly and answered all of our questions. The breakfast is OK but suited towards the sweet-tooth. There were no tea/coffee facilities in the room. There was no ironing board/iron in the room or hotel. The coffee from the machine at breakfast was disappointing.

#Text=Good. Great location just near Roma Termini. Very accommodating given that we had to change rooms because we ended up having an extra person staying with us. Very basic breakfasts, and weird that you had to hand in your room key to the front desk.

#Text=Close to Termina train station. It was very central to the main Termini station.Was clean and tidy.Air conditioned room was nice too.Breakfast was included. The room was very small.Though we were only sleeping there the night after a long flight so it didn't really matter to us.
#Text=Great value for money in a good spot. Ideal location for central station and all sights closeby.
#Text=The Hotel have an amazing location, really close to the main station called "Termini". The Staff. The pictures show something completely different to the real hotel.
#Text=Excellent. hotel was comfortable and bathroom was very good also staff was friendly. room was small but not too small, breakfast was poor.
#Text=Nice choice for 3 star hotel. Great Location, Fair breakfast, Air conditioner. The breakfast could have better bread and some more variety.
